 Zivilrechtsvereinheitlichung bewertet.  a["New Default and Purchasing Law. An Interim Review"]The written version of a lecture given to the Berlin Legal Society. The author makes an initial assessment of the new Default and Purchasing Act two years after the Law of Obligations Modernisation Act came into force. Both the pseudo-problems and the real problems of this area are illustrated here, as are individual questions of the conformity to guidelines of the new Purchasing Act. In particular this advocates a fair interaction with the new law and a discussion free from prejudice. The reform is also evaluated within the context of European Civil Rights Standardisation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aDefault (Law)zGermany. 0aObligations (Law)zGermany. 4aGewährleistung. 4aKaufrecht. 4aSchuldrechtsreform. 7aLAW / Civil Law.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Law - 2000 - 2014z9783110636208oZDB-23-GLA0 cprintz978389949157940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110891584zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110891584zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110891584/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GLAc2000d2014  aZDB-23-GOA